            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Jeremiah.51:54-52:34",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJeremiah%2051%3A54-52%3A34%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_54%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2254%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EBabylon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Complete%20Destruction%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E54%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BListen!%20Hear%20the%20cry%20of%20Babylon%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ethe%20sound%20of%20great%20destruction%20from%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Babylonians.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_55%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2255%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E55%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20destroying%20Babylon.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3EHe%20will%20silence%20her%20loud%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EWaves%20of%20enemies%20pound%20against%20her%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ethe%20noise%20of%20battle%20rings%20through%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_56%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2256%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E56%3C%2Fspan%3EDestroying%20armies%20come%20against%20Babylon.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3EHer%20mighty%20men%20are%20captured%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20their%20weapons%20break%20in%20their%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EFor%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20a%20God%20who%20gives%20just%20punishment%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ehe%20always%20repays%20in%20full.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_57%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2257%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E57%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20will%20make%20her%20officials%20and%20wise%20men%20drunk%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ealong%20with%20her%20captains%2C%20officers%2C%20and%20warriors.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThey%20will%20fall%20asleep%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20never%20wake%20up%20again!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3Esays%20the%20King%2C%20whose%20name%20is%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ethe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Heaven%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Armies.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_58%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2258%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E58%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Heaven%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Armies%20says%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20thick%20walls%20of%20Babylon%20will%20be%20leveled%20to%20the%20ground%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20her%20massive%20gates%20will%20be%20burned.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThe%20builders%20from%20many%20lands%20have%20worked%20in%20vain%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Efor%20their%20work%20will%20be%20destroyed%20by%20fire!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_59%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2259%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJeremiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Message%20Sent%20to%20Babylon%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E59%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20prophet%20Jeremiah%20gave%20this%20message%20to%20Seraiah%20son%20of%20Neriah%20and%20grandson%20of%20Mahseiah%2C%20a%20staff%20officer%2C%20when%20Seraiah%20went%20to%20Babylon%20with%20King%20Zedekiah%20of%20Judah.%20This%20was%20during%20the%20fourth%20year%20of%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E51%3A59%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20fourth%20year%20of%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20was%20593%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_60%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2260%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E60%3C%2Fspan%3EJeremiah%20had%20recorded%20on%20a%20scroll%20all%20the%20terrible%20disasters%20that%20would%20soon%20come%20upon%20Babylon%26%23x2014%3Ball%20the%20words%20written%20here.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_61%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2261%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E61%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20said%20to%20Seraiah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhen%20you%20get%20to%20Babylon%2C%20read%20aloud%20everything%20on%20this%20scroll.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_62%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2262%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E62%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20say%2C%20%26%23x2018%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20you%20have%20said%20that%20you%20will%20destroy%20Babylon%20so%20that%20neither%20people%20nor%20animals%20will%20remain%20here.%20She%20will%20lie%20empty%20and%20abandoned%20forever.%26%23x2019%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_63%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2263%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E63%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20you%20have%20finished%20reading%20the%20scroll%2C%20tie%20it%20to%20a%20stone%20and%20throw%20it%20into%20the%20Euphrates%20River.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_51_64%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2251%22%20vn%3D%2264%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E64%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20say%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BIn%20this%20same%20way%20Babylon%20and%20her%20people%20will%20sink%2C%20never%20again%20to%20rise%2C%20because%20of%20the%20disasters%20I%20will%20bring%20upon%20her.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThis%20is%20the%20end%20of%20Jeremiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_1%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJeremiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E52%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Fall%20of%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EZedekiah%20was%20twenty-one%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20eleven%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Hamutal%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20Jeremiah%20from%20Libnah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_2%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Zedekiah%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20just%20as%20Jehoiakim%20had%20done.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_3%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20things%20happened%20because%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anger%20against%20the%20people%20of%20Jerusalem%20and%20Judah%2C%20until%20he%20finally%20banished%20them%20from%20his%20presence%20and%20sent%20them%20into%20exile.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EZedekiah%20rebelled%20against%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_4%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20on%20January%26%23xA0%3B15%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A4a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eon%20the%20tenth%20day%20of%20the%20tenth%20month%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar.%20A%20number%20of%20events%20in%20Jeremiah%20can%20be%20cross-checked%20with%20dates%20in%20surviving%20Babylonian%20records%20and%20related%20accurately%20to%20our%20modern%20calendar.%20This%20day%20was%20January%26%23xA0%3B15%2C%20588%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20during%20the%20ninth%20year%20of%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A4b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ENebuchadrezzar%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Nebuchadnezzar%3B%20also%20in%2052%3A12%2C%2028%2C%2029%2C%2030.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Babylon%20led%20his%20entire%20army%20against%20Jerusalem.%20They%20surrounded%20the%20city%20and%20built%20siege%20ramps%20against%20its%20walls.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_5%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EJerusalem%20was%20kept%20under%20siege%20until%20the%20eleventh%20year%20of%20King%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_6%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EBy%20July%26%23xA0%3B18%20in%20the%20eleventh%20year%20of%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EBy%20the%20ninth%20day%20of%20the%20fourth%20month%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5Bin%20the%20eleventh%20year%20of%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%5D.%20This%20day%20was%20July%26%23xA0%3B18%2C%20586%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3B%20also%20see%20note%20on%2052%3A4a.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20famine%20in%20the%20city%20had%20become%20very%20severe%2C%20and%20the%20last%20of%20the%20food%20was%20entirely%20gone.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_7%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20a%20section%20of%20the%20city%20wall%20was%20broken%20down%2C%20and%20all%20the%20soldiers%20fled.%20Since%20the%20city%20was%20surrounded%20by%20the%20Babylonians%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A7a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Chaldeans%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20similarly%20in%2052%3A8%2C%2017.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20they%20waited%20for%20nightfall.%20Then%20they%20slipped%20through%20the%20gate%20between%20the%20two%20walls%20behind%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20garden%20and%20headed%20toward%20the%20Jordan%20Valley.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A7b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Arabah.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_8%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20Babylonian%20troops%20chased%20King%20Zedekiah%20and%20overtook%20him%20on%20the%20plains%20of%20Jericho%2C%20for%20his%20men%20had%20all%20deserted%20him%20and%20scattered.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_9%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20captured%20the%20king%20and%20took%20him%20to%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20at%20Riblah%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Hamath.%20There%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20pronounced%20judgment%20upon%20Zedekiah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_10%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20of%20Babylon%20made%20Zedekiah%20watch%20as%20he%20slaughtered%20his%20sons.%20He%20also%20slaughtered%20all%20the%20officials%20of%20Judah%20at%20Riblah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_11%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20gouged%20out%20Zedekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20eyes%20and%20bound%20him%20in%20bronze%20chains%2C%20and%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20led%20him%20away%20to%20Babylon.%20Zedekiah%20remained%20there%20in%20prison%20until%20the%20day%20of%20his%20death.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_12%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Temple%20Destroyed%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20August%26%23xA0%3B17%20of%20that%20year%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A12%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20tenth%20day%20of%20the%20fifth%20month%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar.%20This%20day%20was%20August%26%23xA0%3B17%2C%20586%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3B%20also%20see%20note%20on%2052%3A4a.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20which%20was%20the%20nineteenth%20year%20of%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20Nebuzaradan%2C%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20guard%20and%20an%20official%20of%20the%20Babylonian%20king%2C%20arrived%20in%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_13%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20burned%20down%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20royal%20palace%2C%20and%20all%20the%20houses%20of%20Jerusalem.%20He%20destroyed%20all%20the%20important%20buildings%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Edestroyed%20the%20houses%20of%20all%20the%20important%20people.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20the%20city.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_14%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20supervised%20the%20entire%20Babylonian%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EChaldean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20army%20as%20they%20tore%20down%20the%20walls%20of%20Jerusalem%20on%20every%20side.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_15%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Nebuzaradan%2C%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20guard%2C%20took%20as%20exiles%20some%20of%20the%20poorest%20of%20the%20people%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20people%20who%20remained%20in%20the%20city%2C%20the%20defectors%20who%20had%20declared%20their%20allegiance%20to%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20craftsmen.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_16%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Nebuzaradan%20allowed%20some%20of%20the%20poorest%20people%20to%20stay%20behind%20to%20care%20for%20the%20vineyards%20and%20fields.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_17%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Babylonians%20broke%20up%20the%20bronze%20pillars%20in%20front%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20the%20bronze%20water%20carts%2C%20and%20the%20great%20bronze%20basin%20called%20the%20Sea%2C%20and%20they%20carried%20all%20the%20bronze%20away%20to%20Babylon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_18%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20also%20took%20all%20the%20ash%20buckets%2C%20shovels%2C%20lamp%20snuffers%2C%20basins%2C%20dishes%2C%20and%20all%20the%20other%20bronze%20articles%20used%20for%20making%20sacrifices%20at%20the%20Temple.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_19%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20captain%20of%20the%20guard%20also%20took%20the%20small%20bowls%2C%20incense%20burners%2C%20basins%2C%20pots%2C%20lampstands%2C%20ladles%2C%20bowls%20used%20for%20liquid%20offerings%2C%20and%20all%20the%20other%20articles%20made%20of%20pure%20gold%20or%20silver.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_20%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20weight%20of%20the%20bronze%20from%20the%20two%20pillars%2C%20the%20Sea%20with%20the%20twelve%20bronze%20oxen%20beneath%20it%2C%20and%20the%20water%20carts%20was%20too%20great%20to%20be%20measured.%20These%20things%20had%20been%20made%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20in%20the%20days%20of%20King%20Solomon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_52_21%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2252%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EEach%20of%20the%20pillars%20was%2027%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20tall%20and%2018%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20in%20circumference.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E52%3A21a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E18%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B8.3%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Etall%20and%2012%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B5.5%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Ein%20circumference.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20They%20were%20hollow%2C%20with%20walls%203%26%23xA0%3Binches%